    "summary": "Enterpret exposes two HTTP APIs (Export API and Custom Webhook ingestion) plus a remote MCP server at `https://wisdom-api.enterpret.com/server/mcp`; all require Enterpret-issued credentials, with the MCP supporting either OAuth sign-in or a generated bearer token.",
    "description": "Enterpret is a customer intelligence platform that aggregates feedback from many sources into a knowledge graph for analysis, reporting, and AI-assisted querying. It is used by product and customer experience teams to analyze themes, sentiment, and customer evidence across support, survey, call, and review data.",
    "credentials": {
      "enterpret_api_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Enterpret API token / API key",
        "generateUrl": "https://dashboard.enterpret.com/settings/integrations/",
        "setup": "For Export API access, contact your Customer Success representative to obtain an API token, per the [Data Export API](https://helpcenter.enterpret.com/en/articles/9618433-data-export-api) guide. For Custom Webhook integrations, create an integration in your Enterpret dashboard: go to [Integrations](https://dashboard.enterpret.com/settings/integrations/), click **+New Integration**, choose **Webhook**, finish setup, and copy the API key shown at the top of the integration page, per the [Webhook Integration](https://helpcenter.enterpret.com/en/articles/12131693-webhook-integration) guide. Use it as a Bearer token for export APIs or in the `api-key` header for webhook ingestion."
      },
      "enterpret_mcp_token": {
        "type": "bearer",
        "label": "Enterpret MCP bearer token",
        "generateUrl": "https://dashboard.enterpret.com/settings/mcp/",
        "setup": "In your Enterpret dashboard, go to **Settings → Enterpret MCP** (also referenced as **Settings → MCP** in some guides), click **Generate** under **Auth Token**, then copy the token. This is the easiest manual auth path for MCP clients like Codex and Notion, per the [Enterpret MCP Server](https://helpcenter.enterpret.com/en/articles/12665166-enterpret-mcp-server) and [Enterpret in Notion Custom Agents](https://helpcenter.enterpret.com/en/articles/14668232-enterpret-in-notion-custom-agents) guides."
      },
      "enterpret_mcp_oauth": {
        "type": "oauth2",
        "label": "Enterpret MCP OAuth authorization",
        "setup": "Use an MCP client that supports remote server sign-in, then connect to `https://wisdom-api.enterpret.com/server/mcp` and complete the Enterpret sign-in / authorize window when prompted. The Help Center shows this flow for Claude Code (`/mcp` → **Authenticate**), Notion (**Sign in with your Enterpret account and authorize access**), and Glean (**Authentication: OAuth (recommended)**) in the [Enterpret MCP Server](https://helpcenter.enterpret.com/en/articles/12665166-enterpret-mcp-server) and [Enterpret in Notion Custom Agents](https://helpcenter.enterpret.com/en/articles/14668232-enterpret-in-notion-custom-agents) guides."
      }
    },
